  <section>
    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p>All <code>data-field</code> paths are validated against a strict regex. Only simple property access is allowed:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Allowed:</strong> <code>name</code>, <code>user.email</code>, <code>items[0].title</code></li>
      <li><strong>Rejected:</strong> <code>price.toFixed(2)</code>, <code>`${price}`</code>, <code>price * 1.1</code>, <code>stock > 0 ? 'yes' : 'no'</code></li>
    </ul>
    <p>Invalid paths log a console warning and resolve to empty content.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Progressive Enhancement</h2>
    <p>Without JavaScript, the <code>&lt;template&gt;</code> is hidden by default. Consider providing a <code>&lt;noscript&gt;</code> fallback or static content before the template for no-JS contexts.</p>
  </section>

